review_text:
Posted: October 14
An awesome third-person action RPG with a great atmosphere, challenging combat and outstanding visual design. Overall, it's an amazing game and a great ending to an incredible trilogy. However, don't believe the internet hype — it's not a flawless masterpiece. It has some questionable areas and lacks innovation, but it's still a must-play for any self-respecting gamer.

Pros:
- Wonderful soundtrack;
- Responsive controls;
- Good enemy variety;
- Attention to detail;
- Interesting story and lore;
- A dreary and depressing atmosphere;
- Outstanding art style and visuals;
- Satisfying and challenging gameplay;
- Great replayability;
- Memorable characters;
- Amazing level design;
- Great optimisation;
- An interesting multiplayer system;
- Awesome boss fights;
- Great voice acting;

Cons:
- Too similar to the first game in many ways;
- A lot of enemies and some bosses are very annoying;
- Keyboard and mouse are not prompted;

Posted: April 27
try finger,
but hole

Posted: April 25
Better gameplay than the first and second, more varied builds, as well as the player's movesets;
Mobs also have better movesets, as well as bosses have better fights;
Incredible scenarios, graphics have evolved as expected;
It still doesn't have the map backtracking of the first game, but it's better than the second game.
I just found it less striking than the first, and the bonfire link of the second one is still my favorite.

in short:: apart from how striking the first one is, and how good the backtracking is, and the bonfire link of the second one, this one is better in every other way, just play it.

Posted: March 13
