Posted: January 26
Dark Souls III itself feels raw and undone;
Achievements are awful, especially "Master of Rings" with requires you grind covenants and beat game 3 times to find all rings +1 +2 included with can be found only during NG+ and NG++ respectfully;
Bosses sometimes feels like a lame mob with boss heals bar, or they're hitting like a truck, beating cr*ap out of you and throwing you from a bridge. Yes, Dragon Slayer's Armor, I'm talking about you;
DLC's are great, especially 'The Ringed City' where you are fighting Slave Knight Gael in a pile of ash at the end of a time;
Overall, I'm forced myself to get 100% of Achievements, beat the game 3 times, complete DLC's, and it was fun (sometime frustrating) experience;
